<!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
<div class="main-wrap">

  <!--  CONTENT  -->
  <main class="content">
    <p>
      St Francis Girls Suwerwa is a top-performing school located in Trans Nzoia County, Kenya. 
      The School is well-known for its academic and co-curricular excellence, offering a vibrant, 
      stimulating learning environment that prioritizes the holistic development of students.
    </p>
    <p>
      SFGS provides a rigorous academic program that prepares students for success in higher education 
      and beyond. The School has a highly qualified teaching staff who use modern teaching techniques 
      to make learning more engaging, interactive and memorable. Whether in mathematics, science, 
      humanities, or languages, the school's curriculum is designed to challenge students and aim for 
      intellectual growth.
    </p>
    <p>
      The school's emphasis on co-curricular activities enables students to develop skills and talents 
      that complement their academic studies. With a well-established library, well-equipped classrooms, 
      and modern facilities, students at St Francis Girls Suwerwa are assured of quality learning experiences.
    </p>
    <p>
      The school offers a diverse and supportive environment that encourages students to develop into 
      well-rounded individuals. With active clubs and societies, peer mentoring, and counseling services 
      on campus, SFGS creates a supportive community that fosters lifelong learning. The School has a 
      rich culture that values respect, discipline, and responsibility.
    </p>
    <p>
      We have a long-standing tradition of producing notable alumni who have made significant contributions 
      to society. The school's alumni are highly respected in fields such as medicine, politics, business, 
      and education. Studying at St Francis Girls Suwerwa opens doors to extensive opportunities for 
      networking and mentorship.
    </p>

    <!-- Three Pillars -->
    <div class="section-block">
      <h3>What Sets Us Apart</h3>
      <div class="pillars">
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar-icon"></div>
          <h4>Academic Excellence</h4>
          <p>Consistent top KCSE performance driven by qualified staff and modern teaching.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar-icon"></div>
          <h4>Christian Foundation</h4>
          <p>All endeavors anchored in Christian values, integrity, and fear of the Lord.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar-icon"></div>
          <h4>Holistic Growth</h4>
          <p>Sports, clubs, leadership, and arts complement classroom learning.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Curriculum -->
    <div class="section-block">
      <h3>Curriculum</h3>
      <p>
        In the first two years, students take a rich blend of compulsory and optional subjects 
        designed to build a solid academic foundation. From Form Three, students sit a minimum 
        of 7 subjects in the KCSE examination as per KNEC guidelines  most students opt for 8.
      </p>
      <div class="subjects-grid">
        <div class="subject-card">
          <h4>Compulsory Subjects</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Mathematics</li>
            <li>English</li>
            <li>Kiswahili</li>
            <li>Biology</li>
            <li>Chemistry</li>
            <li>Physics</li>
            <li>Geography</li>
            <li>History</li>
            <li>Christian Religious Education</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="subject-card">
          <h4>Optional Subjects (choose one)</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Agriculture</li>
            <li>Business Studies</li>
            <li>French</li>
            <li>Computer Studies</li>
            <li>German</li>
            <li>Music</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="optional-note">
        <strong>KCSE Examination:</strong> From Form 3 onwards, students are examined on a 
        minimum of <strong>7 subjects</strong> and a maximum of <strong>8 subjects</strong> 
        as per Kenya National Examinations Council (KNEC) guidelines.
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Location -->
    <div class="location-callout">
      <div class="loc-icon"></div>
      <div>
        <h4>Our Location</h4>
        <p>
          St Francis Girls Suwerwa is situated <strong>20 km from Nakuru town</strong> in Kenya's 
          Rift Valley. The school shares its beautiful compound with <strong>Kabarak University</strong>, 
          creating a unique academic ecosystem that inspires students toward higher education.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
